{"questionId":"27728","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the vectors <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">j</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">j</mi></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> be the angle between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the exact value of the limit approached by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>→</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>→</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>the limit is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></math>. Do not accept rounded values such as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>785</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27728","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the exact value of the limit approached by θ as n→∞.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}